1
00:02:04,599 --> 00:02:05,079
Brother

2
00:02:06,079 --> 00:02:07,439
We need your fingerprint authorization here.

3
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,560
I just heard the cops were planning a surprise raid.

4
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,000
I thought we were done for this time.

5
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:12,960
Luckily, your deployment was solid.

6
00:02:13,159 --> 00:02:13,960
And you arrived just in time.

7
00:02:14,639 --> 00:02:15,599
Before that guy Zhou got on the island,

8
00:02:15,599 --> 00:02:16,599
everything was already taken care of.

9
00:02:16,919 --> 00:02:17,719
Even dogs wouldn't be able to sniff it out.

10
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,280
You all leave for now.

11
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:32,520
Yes, sir.

12
00:02:38,439 --> 00:02:39,759
Superintendent Zhou, you really are dedicated.

13
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,879
Back to work as soon as your injuries healed.

14
00:02:42,479 --> 00:02:43,960
So conscientious even during a typhoon.

15
00:02:46,479 --> 00:02:48,080
Mr. Ji is the one who is truly conscientious.

16
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:49,759
On a typhoon day,

17
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,199
mobilizing so many people to go out to sea.

18
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:54,599
It seems this shipment is very important to you.

19
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,280
These are all flood control supplies for donation.

20
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,039
Of course they are important.

21
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,479
Superintendent Zhou, you've been inspecting all the way here.

22
00:03:04,479 --> 00:03:05,439
Checking everything...

23
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:06,800
Did you find anything?

24
00:03:09,319 --> 00:03:09,879
Indeed.

25
00:03:12,439 --> 00:03:13,639
They are all flood control supplies.

26
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,080
There are no issues.

27
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:21,000
Then it seems Superintendent Zhou's intel is often wrong.

28
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:23,800
Since there are no issues here,

29
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,960
and if there is nothing else,

30
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,879
I will take my leave first.

31
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:29,159
If you still want to inspect,

32
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,879
you can continue. Take your time.

33
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,159
Or you can hang out here for a while.

34
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,960
I'll have my men keep you good company.

35
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,639
You were there the day Superintendent Guan died, right?

36
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,439
And Superintendent Guan's adopted daughter,

37
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:51,719
Hao Yu.

38
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,879
Actually, I've always wanted to summon her.

39
00:03:55,879 --> 00:03:56,719
To ask her some questions properly.

40
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,560
Come to think of it, we are old acquaintances.

41
00:04:05,719 --> 00:04:08,000
I must have known her

42
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,879
longer than you have, Mr. Ji.

43
00:04:12,199 --> 00:04:13,560
For the sake of our old acquaintance,

44
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,720
she should be willing to chat with me a bit more.

45
00:04:17,879 --> 00:04:19,240
To tell me the details of that day.

46
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:28,600
Is that so?

47
00:06:11,879 --> 00:06:12,879
Password correct.

48
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,800
Before that day,

49
00:06:27,519 --> 00:06:28,920
I had been away on a business trip.

50
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:30,879
As soon as I got back,

51
00:06:30,879 --> 00:06:32,839
Hao Yu missed me like a newlywed.

52
00:06:33,079 --> 00:06:35,519
We didn't leave the bed from morning till night.

53
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:39,920
Unless...

54
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,560
she split herself in two to go to Wugang Street?

55
00:06:52,439 --> 00:06:52,959
Brother Jie.

56
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,079
The power is out at home.

57
00:06:54,199 --> 00:06:55,240
All the surveillance cameras at home are down.

58
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:56,879
It's probably because of the typhoon.

59
00:06:57,279 --> 00:06:58,439
It's pitch black at home right now.

60
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:02,720
Did you call Hao Yu?

61
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,319
Isn't there a backup power supply at home?

62
00:07:04,439 --> 00:07:05,120
Where are the others?

63
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,920
They said they were worried about their own houses.

64
00:07:07,399 --> 00:07:08,680
Madam let them all go back.

65
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,480
Now we can't reach Madam either.

66
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:12,600
Have Fei Hu ready the car. I'm going back now.

67
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,199
Mr. Ji.

68
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,759
The sea route is closed now.

69
00:07:16,639 --> 00:07:17,600
You can only take the mountain road.

70
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,439
The mountain road at this time...

71
00:07:19,519 --> 00:07:20,519
I'm afraid there might be mudslides.

72
00:07:21,079 --> 00:07:22,000
As a law enforcement officer,

73
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,680
I don't wish for anything bad to happen.

74
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:27,319
You may have known Hao Yu longer than I have,

75
00:07:28,199 --> 00:07:28,879
but right now, I feel that

76
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,360
you are merely acquaintances.

77
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,279
After all, you don't even know what she's afraid of.

78
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,480
I don't know what tricks you're trying to pull,

79
00:07:37,839 --> 00:07:38,759
but let me tell you,

80
00:07:39,279 --> 00:07:40,279
this is my territory.

81
00:07:40,879 --> 00:07:42,399
You should worry about yourself.

82
00:07:45,079 --> 00:07:46,480
Don't accidentally fall into the sea.

83
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:01,920
Brother Jie, don't worry about the cargo.

84
00:08:02,279 --> 00:08:03,079
Don't worry about Madam.

85
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:03,600
How about I go?

86
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,360
You guys watch this place.

87
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,680
I know this road well. I'll be fine.

88
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:04,720
Pick up the phone.

89
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:10,440
Pick up the phone, Hao Yu.

90
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,000
Pick up.

91
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:18,559
Hao Yu, pick up the phone.

92
00:11:21,559 --> 00:11:22,519
Pick up the phone, Hao Yu.

93
00:11:57,039 --> 00:11:58,360
The number you have dialed

94
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,799
is temporarily unanswered.

95
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,559
Please try again later.

96
00:12:01,639 --> 00:12:02,399
Sorry.

97
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:22,919
Hey, Hao Yu.

98
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,639
Hao Yu, can you hear me?

99
00:12:26,759 --> 00:12:27,399
Hao Yu, hold on a little longer.

100
00:12:27,559 --> 00:12:28,399
I'll be right back.

101
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,320
Listen to me now.

102
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:31,279
Take a deep breath.

103
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,600
Hao Yu, are you listening? Hao Yu.

104
00:12:37,159 --> 00:12:37,879
Follow my lead.

105
00:12:38,759 --> 00:12:39,600
Hold on a little longer.

106
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:40,960
We'll be home soon.

107
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,720
Deep breaths. Deep breaths.

108
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,559
Inhale. Exhale.

109
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,039
Inhale.

110
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:49,679
Inhale.

111
00:12:50,039 --> 00:12:50,559
Exhale.

112
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:52,080
Inhale.

113
00:12:52,799 --> 00:12:53,480
Exhale.

114
00:12:55,159 --> 00:12:55,879
Inhale.

115
00:12:57,519 --> 00:12:58,039
Exhale.

116
00:13:00,399 --> 00:13:01,039
Inhale.

117
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:02,759
Exhale.

118
00:13:04,399 --> 00:13:05,000
Inhale.

119
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:09,360
We'll be home soon. Just hold on.

120
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,039
Hao Yu, hold on a little longer.

121
00:13:11,039 --> 00:13:11,679
I'll be right back.

122
00:13:11,879 --> 00:13:12,679
It won't take more than half an hour.

123
00:13:12,879 --> 00:13:13,480
Do you hear me?

124
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:24,600
Hao Yu.

125
00:13:29,639 --> 00:13:30,200
Hao Yu.

126
00:16:44,519 --> 00:16:45,039
Hao Yu.

127
00:16:48,919 --> 00:16:49,399
Hao Yu.

128
00:17:02,559 --> 00:17:03,000
Hao Yu.

129
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:15,640
Hao Yu.

130
00:17:23,519 --> 00:17:24,039
Hao Yu.

131
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:32,160
Hao Yu.

132
00:17:37,599 --> 00:17:38,119
Hao Yu.

133
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:04,799
Hao Yu.

134
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,240
Hao Yu.

135
00:18:47,799 --> 00:18:48,400
It's okay now.

136
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,200
I was looking for you everywhere just now.

137
00:18:53,079 --> 00:18:54,359
I thought something happened to you.

138
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:02,359
The power suddenly went out while I was showering.

139
00:19:02,839 --> 00:19:04,400
Then I came down to look for candles.

140
00:19:05,079 --> 00:19:06,720
I dropped my phone somewhere and couldn't find it.

141
00:19:08,119 --> 00:19:08,880
It was too dark.

142
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:11,920
I was so scared.

143
00:19:12,119 --> 00:19:13,319
I couldn't see anything.

144
00:19:18,319 --> 00:19:18,759
Don't be afraid.

145
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:19,720
It's okay now.

146
00:19:20,079 --> 00:19:21,119
I'm back now, aren't I?

147
00:19:23,359 --> 00:19:26,079
I thought I'd never see you again.

148
00:19:30,119 --> 00:19:30,920
It's my fault.

149
00:19:31,559 --> 00:19:32,319
It's my fault.

150
00:19:33,759 --> 00:19:35,599
I should have explained things clearly before I left.

151
00:19:36,279 --> 00:19:37,279
I shouldn't have made you angry.

152
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:41,119
I should have told the servants before I left...

153
00:19:41,119 --> 00:19:42,720
...to take good care of you and watch over you.

154
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,119
Then nothing would have happened to you.

155
00:20:01,839 --> 00:20:03,000
The warning is in effect.

156
00:20:03,359 --> 00:20:04,160
The sea routes are all closed.

157
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,839
How did you get back?

158
00:20:09,839 --> 00:20:10,960
I took Eagle's Beak Cliff.

159
00:20:13,599 --> 00:20:16,079
I've taken it a few times before to hide from the cops.

160
00:20:16,559 --> 00:20:18,119
It's just that there's a typhoon outside today.

161
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:19,519
So it took a little longer.

162
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:23,759
You risked your life to rush back...

163
00:20:23,839 --> 00:20:25,200
...just because you were worried I'd be scared of the dark?

164
00:20:32,599 --> 00:20:33,480
I'm fine.

165
00:20:36,119 --> 00:20:36,880
I'm really fine.

166
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:39,839
When everything is over tomorrow...

167
00:20:40,319 --> 00:20:41,240
...we'll leave this place.

168
00:20:42,799 --> 00:20:44,000
Everything will be alright.

169
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:49,400
By the way.

170
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:54,079
It's past midnight now.

171
00:21:20,039 --> 00:21:21,000
Today is the anniversary...

172
00:21:21,079 --> 00:21:22,240
...of our five years together.

173
00:21:24,319 --> 00:21:26,000
And the day I want to put a ring on your finger.

174
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:32,200
I originally thought...

175
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,960
...I'd tell you tomorrow after we fly to the UK.

176
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:37,359
But today you got jealous again...

177
00:21:37,559 --> 00:21:38,519
...and got scared.

178
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:40,680
We have a long flight tomorrow.

179
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:43,480
You need some comfort.

180
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:47,160
This is pretty good.

181
00:22:59,359 --> 00:22:59,880
Uncle Kun.
